 to contribute at some point guidelines for giving tea talks can be found here the current tea talk schedulers are oliver hahn and matthew kerr we have a number of mechanisms in place for making the astro ph discussion efficient this is important given the bewildering deluge of new papers being produced by the community guidelines for presenting a paper can be found here there is a cosmocoffee message board of interesting papers to be discussed at tea time please add papers you think will be interesting to the group the message board managers can help you contribute to this list if you are new if you want to bring a paper up for discussion or feel you don t have the time or the expertise to explain it properly you can suggest in the comments field some names from this list of expert postdoc reviewers who can read it for the group for next time this is especially useful for busy faculty and keen to learn students all attendees are strongly encouraged to post their own papers too here is a list of recent kipac papers we also have a forum for discussing articles in the general news about astrophysics and cosmology post links to newspapers tv clips blogs etc here start date title description location mar 20 2012 11 00 am kipac tea talk yao yuan mao kipac velocity distribution of dark matter in the milky way campus varian room 355 mar 23 2012 10 30 am kipac tea talk brian gerke lbl the past present and future of energy efficiency standards slac fkb 3rd floor conf room mar 27 2012 11 00 am no kipac tea talk spring break mar 30 2012 10 30 am no kipac tea talk spring break apr 03 2012 11 00 am kipac tea talk chihway chang kipac tba campus varian room 355 apr 06 2012 10 30 am kipac tea talk jack singal kipac tba slac fkb 3rd floor conf room apr 10 2012 11 00 am kipac tea talk zeeshan ahmed kipac tba campus varian room 355 apr 13 2012 10 30 am kipac tea talk mark hertzberg sitp & kipac tba slac fkb 3rd floor conf room apr 20 2012 10 30 am kipac tea talk jeffrey oishi kipac tb